The paper deals with capacity analysis of communication channels, specifically Gaussian interference channels. This falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses multiple access outerbounds, which is related to Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of multiple carriers and power allocation is related to Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses encoding techniques, which is related to Cryptography and Security (cs.CC) sub-category.
